ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ’¼ Seller Performance Analysis

A small group of sellers generates a disproportionately large share of revenue, indicating seller dependency within the marketplace.

Key Observation:
Some sellers achieve high revenue with fewer orders (high-value products), while others rely on high order volume with lower revenue per order.

ğŸšš Freight & Logistics Impact

Freight cost forms a significant portion of product pricing:

Average freight cost: R$ 20

Average product price: R$ 120

Certain categories show very high freight-to-price ratios, which may negatively affect conversion rates.

Actionable Insight:
Logistics optimization and bundled pricing could improve customer satisfaction and sales in freight-heavy categories.

ğŸ‘¥ Customer Behavior Analysis

One-time Customers: 90,542

Repeat Customers: 2,800

Although repeat customers are fewer, they contribute a higher average lifetime value.

Key Metrics:

Avg CLV (One-time): R$ 160.77

Avg CLV (Repeat): R$ 308.59

Insight:
Customer retention represents a major growth opportunity, as repeat customers generate nearly 2Ã— higher lifetime value.

ğŸ§  Key Business Takeaways

Customer retention is a critical growth lever.

Revenue is highly concentrated across specific sellers, products, and categories.

Premium categories and high-CLV customers offer high ROI targeting opportunities.

Freight cost optimization can significantly improve purchasing decisions and profitability.

